Name :
	xor.py - Decrypt or Encrypt an xor cipher message

Synopsis:
	xor.py -m (the message) -k (the key) -o (the type of output int , hex , ascii , bin)

Input :
	-m      allows you to specify the message to decrypt (if there is space between the characters you must use quotation mark)
	
	-k      specify the key for decrypt the message the key can be larger and smaller than the message !

	-fm     you can use file to specify the message but it only decrypt the content of the file !

	-fk     same for the key use a file for specify it !

	note :  you can use all of this type in input : bin , int , hex and  ascii
output :

	-o      it is a very simple use just pass in argument after -o the type of output
	
	ps :    for redirect the output of this command use '>' and the file where you want to save the output !

format of input :

	normally the format of input is recognized automatically but if there is some ambiguity you can specify it !

	exemple : ascii (face)  / hex (face) == int(64206) or 
		int(1010) / bin (1010) = int(10)

	-mt     specify the type of the message work also with file

	-kt     specify the type of the key work also with file 

	
